com.experian.aperture.datastudio.sdk.testframework

Class TestSession

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.experian.aperture.datastudio.sdk.testframework.TestSession

  • public class TestSession
extends Object
    The test session that target a specific custom step. This class is responsible for initializing custom step's stepOutput and execution.
    Since:
    1.0.0

    • Method Detail

      • initialise

        protected TestSession initialise()
        Initialises the custom step with all the callbacks functions required. Calls the custom step's initialise function. Ensures that the columns are distinctly named.
        Returns:
        TestSession
        Throws:
        SDKTestException - if there is an error during the initialisation of the custom step

      • execute

        public SDKAssertion execute()
        Executes the custom step.

        Execution will call StepOutput.baseInitialize and StepOutput.baseExecute only when the StepConfiguration.isComplete return True or null (as per Aperture Data Studio existing behavior).

        Returns:
        SDKAssertion - a standard assertion objects to verify the result of custom step execution.
        Throws:
        SDKTestException - if there is an error executing the custom step. SDKTestException will wrap SDKException.
        SDKTestException - if StepConfiguration.isComplete return False.
        Since:
        1.0.0
